50|$|Falconer {{became a}} flatmate of Tony Blair {{when they were}} both young barristers in London in the late 1970s in Wandsworth, having first met as pupils at rival Scottish schools in the 1960s. While Blair went into politics, Falconer {{concentrated}} on his legal career. He practised from Fountain Court <b>Chambers</b> <b>in</b> London, and became a Queen's <b>Counsel</b> <b>in</b> 1991.|$|R
